<reference id="author" xml:lang="en-us">
<title><xmlelement>author</xmlelement></title>
<shortdesc>An author is the entity that created the content, <ph
      rev="review-g">such as a person, organization, or
    application.</ph></shortdesc>
<prolog><metadata>
<keywords>
        <indexterm>elements<indexterm>prolog<indexterm><xmlelement>author</xmlelement></indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
<indexterm>prolog elements<indexterm><xmlelement>author</xmlelement></indexterm></indexterm>
</keywords>
</metadata>
    <metadata/></prolog>
<refbody>
    <section id="usage-information">
      <title>Usage information</title>
      <p>The <xmlelement>author</xmlelement> element is equivalent to the
          <xmlelement>Creator</xmlelement> element in Dublin Core.</p>
    </section>
    <section id="attributes">
      <title>Attributes</title>
      <div conkeyref="reuse-attributes/author-attributes"/>
    </section>
<example id="example" otherprops="examples">
<title>Example</title>
      <p>The following code sample shows that two people contributed to the
        topic:</p>
<codeblock>&lt;prolog&gt;
    <b>&lt;author type="creator"&gt;Jane&lt;/author&gt;
    &lt;author type="contributor"&gt;John&lt;/author&gt;</b>
&lt;/prolog&gt;</codeblock>
      <p>Jane is specified as a creator of the topic, and John is specified
        as a contributor to the topic.</p>

</example>
</refbody>
</reference>

